how to create a component:

1st way:
1. create a folder
2. we need to create 4 files inside it
    a. login.component.ts
    b. login.component.html
    c. login.component.css
    d. login.component.spec.ts
3. register login component inside app.module.ts
4. use selector of the component and use it inside the files where we want it   

2nd way:
you need to go to cli and enter one single line command 
    ng generate component login
    or
    ng g c login

3.steps for passing value from parent component to child component    

1. create variable in parent component
2. pass this variable to child
3. goto template of parent and pass the value through property binding
4. create Input variable in child
5. display in template of child component
6. add the selector of parent into app.component.html

4. steps for passing value from child to parent component
a. in child component create a event(button click), this event 
will get value displayed from parent
b. it has to emit it to parent i.e inform parent to show the value
c. by creating a output variable we will be able to emit it i.e pass instruction to parent to show that value
d. parent will receive it from selector of child component present in parent template
e. it will call showmonth() and will display the value

routing :

1. create a header component and add navbar to it
2. goto app.routingmodule.ts and configure paths
3. add it to app.component.html along with router outlet

services:

1. create a angular service and add methods to it so that it will receive observable object as response
2. in app module .ts add httpclientmodule
3. create component
4. subscribe to receive endpoints